Sentencas: Many of the challenges in solid oxide fuel cell technology stem from chemical and mechanical incompatibilities between the anode, cathode and electrolyte materials.
Titulo: Performance of a single layer fuel cell based on a mixed proton-electron conducting composite

Sentencas: Numerous attempts have been made to identify compatible materials.
Titulo: Performance of a single layer fuel cell based on a mixed proton-electron conducting composite

Sentencas: Here, these challenges are circumvented by the introduction of a working single layer fuel cell, fabricated from a composite of proton conducting BaCe0.6Zr0.2Y0.2O3-delta and a mixture of semiconducting oxides - Li2O, NiO, and ZnO. Structural and electrical properties of the composite, related to its fuel cell performance are investigated.
Titulo: Performance of a single layer fuel cell based on a mixed proton-electron conducting composite

Sentencas: The single layer fuel cell shows a maximum OCV of 0.83 V and a peak power density of 3.86 mW cm(-2) at 600 degrees C. Activation and mass transport losses are identified as the major limiting factor for efficiency and power output.
Titulo: Performance of a single layer fuel cell based on a mixed proton-electron conducting composite
